Package weka.dl4j.zoo.keras

Class KerasZooModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.deeplearning4j.zoo.ZooModel
      • weka.dl4j.zoo.keras.KerasZooModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.deeplearning4j.zoo.InstantiableModel
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DenseNet, EfficientNet, InceptionResNetV2, InceptionV3, MobileNet, NASNet, ResNet, VGG, Xception
    public abstract class KerasZooModel
extends org.deeplearning4j.zoo.ZooModel
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class essentially copies DL4J's ZooModel class, allowing the custom Keras models to provide the same interface as those models provided by DL4J. It was originally created as KerasZooModels were loaded from the .h5 file, so they couldn't use DL4J's ZooModel implementation (as it loads model from the native .zip format). Loading from .h5 format is a little unreliable at times so this class uses the native DL4J .zip format. This implementation is different in that the pretrained URL and checksum are taken from the KerasConstants file - a global constant which defines these values. This is easier to manage than having URLs and checksums in each individual model class (as is done in DL4J).
